#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:1
msgid "Google Single Sign-On (E20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:4
msgid ""
"Follow these steps to configure Mattermost to use Google as a single "
"sign-on (SSO) service for team creation, account creation and sign-in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:6
msgid ""
"Note: Google SSO is not yet supported in the mobile app. If you want to "
"use Google SSO on mobile, you'll have to build your own app."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:8
msgid ""
"Note: The Google People API has replaced the Google+ API, which was "
"deprecated by Google as of March 7th, 2019 per their notice at "
"https://developers.google.com/+/api-shutdown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:10
msgid ""
"1 - Go to Google API Manager, click Credentials in the left hand sidebar,"
" click Create a project and enter \"Mattermost - your-company-name\" as "
"the Project Name, then click Create."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:14
msgid "2 - In the Dashboard click the option to ENABLE APIS AND SERVICES."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:18
msgid ""
"Once in the API Library, scroll down to Google People API and click "
"Enable in the header. This might take a few minutes to propagate through "
"Google's systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:20
msgid ""
"3 - Leave the Google+ API menu to return to the APIs & Services menu. In "
"the left hand sidebar select Credentials, click the OAuth consent screen "
"header and enter \"Mattermost\" as the Application Name, then click Save."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:24
msgid ""
"Scroll further down to add your Mattermost instance to a list of "
"authorized domains that can access the API. For example, if it is hosted "
"on mattermost.yourdomain.com add yourdomain.com."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:28
msgid ""
"4 - Select Credentials and click Create credentials, then choose OAuth "
"client ID from the drop-down list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:32
msgid ""
"5 - Select Web Application as the Application type, and choose a "
"descriptive Name for the OAuth connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:34
msgid ""
"Under Restrictions > Authorized redirect URIs, enter your-mattermost-"
"url/signup/google/complete (example: "
"http://localhost:8065/signup/google/complete). Click Create."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:38
msgid ""
"6 - Copy the Client ID and Client Secret, which will be used to configure"
" Google SSO for Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:42
msgid ""
"7 - In System Console > OAuth 2.0 > Select OAuth 2.0 service provider, "
"choose Google Apps as the service provider and enter Client ID and Client"
" Secret from step 6 in their respective fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:44
msgid "8 - Restart your Mattermost server to see the changes take effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:46
msgid "Notes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:47
msgid ""
"You may also enter Client ID and Client Secret fields from step 6 "
"directly in GoogleSettings section of config/config.json."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:48
msgid ""
"The following default values in GoogleSettings section of "
"config/config.json are recommended:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:49
msgid "Scope: profile email"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:50
msgid "AuthEndpoint: https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:51
msgid "TokenEndpoint: https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v4/token"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/deployment/sso-google.md:52
msgid ""
"UserApiEndpoint: "
"https://people.googleapis.com/v1/people/me?personFields=names,emailAddresses,nicknames,metadata"
msgstr ""

